  "content": "To solve this problem, we need to find the value of \\( k = F_{13} - 230 \\), where \\( F_m \\) is the \\( m \\)-th Fibonacci number with \\( F_1 = 1 \\), \\( F_2 = 1 \\), and \\( F_m = F_{m-1} + F_{m-2} \\) for \\( m \\ge 3 \\).\n\nFirst, let's calculate the Fibonacci numbers up to \\( F_{13} \\):\n\n\\[\n\\begin{align*}\nF_1 &= 1, \\\\\nF_2 &= 1, \\\\\nF_3 &= F_2 + F_1 = 1 + 1 = 2, \\\\\nF_4 &= F_3 + F_2 = 2 + 1 = 3, \\\\\nF_5 &= F_4 + F_3 = 3 + 2 = 5, \\\\\nF_6 &= F_5 + F_4 = 5 + 3 = 8, \\\\\nF_7 &= F_6 + F_5 = 8 + 5 = 13, \\\\\nF_8 &= F_7 + F_6 = 13 + 8 = 21, \\\\\nF_9 &= F_8 + F_7 = 21 + 13 = 34, \\\\\nF_{10} &= F_9 + F_8 = 34 + 21 = 55, \\\\\nF_{11} &= F_{10} + F_9 = 55 + 34 = 89, \\\\\nF_{12} &= F_{11} + F_{10} = 89 + 55 = 144, \\\\\nF_{13} &= F_{12} + F_{11} = 144 + 89 = 233.\n\\end{align*}\n\\]\n\nNow, we can find \\( k \\):\n\n\\[\nk = F_{13} - 230 = 233 - 230 = 3.\n\\]\n\nTherefore, the final answer is:\n\n\\[\n\\boxed{3}\n\\]",
